=== Long Track Challenge ===
*25 September 2010
*{{flagicon|FIN}} [[Forssa]], [[Tavastia Proper]]
*Pilvenmäki (trotting track) (Length: 1.000 m)
*Referee: {{flagicon|FRA}} Thierry Bouin
*Jury President: {{flagicon|GBR}} Anthony Noel
*''References'' <ref name="speedway-org"/><ref>{{cite web | title = Supplementary Regulations Long Track Challenge | publisher = FIM-live.com | date =  | url = http://www.fim-live.com/fileadmin/alfresco/Manifestations/Forssan_MM_lisaem._2010.pdf | accessdate = 2010-07-31 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Ballot Long Track Challenge | publisher = FIM-live.com | date =  | url = http://www.fim-live.com/fileadmin/alfresco/Manifestations/Ballot_Challenge_Forssa.pdf | accessdate = 2010-09-20 }}</ref>
*Qualified riders:
**The 12 top placed riders from the Qualification rounds. If a rider is not able to take part in the Long Track Challenge, he will be replaced by the next placed rider from his last Qualification Meeting.
**Riders placed eight to thirteen from the 2010 World Championship final classification. If a rider is not able to take part in the Long Track Challenge, he will be replaced by the next placed rider on the Final Classification list.
**Track reserve riders: Two riders nominated by the host national federation.
*Changes:
