| location          = [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], Dominican Republic [[File:Flag of the Dominican Republic.svg|20px]]
| coordinates       = {{Coord|19|28|1|N|70|42|32|W|type:landmark_scale:2000|display=it}}
| opened            = October 25, 1958
| operator          = [[Águilas Cibaeñas]]
| surface           = Grass
| tenants           = [[Águilas Cibaeñas]], [[Dominican Winter Baseball League]]
| seating_capacity  = 18,077
| dimensions        = '''Left Field''' – {{Convert|335|ft|m|0}}<br />'''Center Field''' – {{Convert|385|ft|m|0}}<br />'''Right Field''' – {{Convert|335|ft|m|0}}
}}
'''Estadio Cibao''' is a multi-use stadium in [[Santiago de los Caballeros|Santiago]], Dominican Republic.  Currently, it is mostly used for baseball games and hosts the home games of the [[Águilas Cibaeñas]] in the [[Dominican Winter Baseball League]].  The stadium opened on October 25, 1958 and was constructed by the engineer Bienvenido Martinez Brea.<ref name="Bajo Techo">{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/bajotecho/docs/bajo_techo_2|title=Estadios de Beisball Dominicanos |publisher=Bajo Techo Revista Inmobiliaria|accessdate=2010-07-22|year=2008}}</ref> Estadio Cibao seats 18,077 spectators, making it the largest in the [[Dominican Republic]].<ref name="ESPN.com">{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/mlb/worldclassic2006/news/story?id=2291226|title=Welcome to the Dominican Republic |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=2010-07-22|year=2006}}</ref> Its field dimensions are 335 feet at the foul poles, 365 feet at the power alleys and 385 feet at center field.

In 2008, Estadio Cibao exclusively hosted the [[2008 Caribbean Series|Caribbean Series]] for the first time. Yet, this was the second time in the [[Dominican Republic]] that series was played outside [[Estadio Quisqueya]] (the first was in 1976, when the venues were split).

[[File:Estadiocibao.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Main Entrance into Estadio Cibao]]

==Estadio Cibao renovation==

In 2007 [[Leonel Fernández|President Leonel Fernández]] initiated a renovation project of the stadium in time to host the 2008 Caribbean  Series.<ref name="El Nuevo Diarrio">{{cite web|url=http://elnuevodiario.com.do/app/article.aspx?id=52427|title=LF anuncia inversión millonaria en obras para el Cibao |publisher=El Nuevo Diarrio.com|accessdate=2010-07-22|year=2007}}</ref> The project included extending the visitors club house, remodeling the main entrance, construction of a multi-use stage behind center field and construction of both a new batting cage and a bull pen.<ref name="El Nuevo Diarrio.com">{{cite web|url=http://elnuevodiario.com.do/app/article.aspx?id=89107|title=Obras Públicas entrega Estadio Cibao |publisher=El Nuevo Diarrio.com|accessdate=2010-07-22|year=2008}}</ref>  The renovation, priced at $110,320,921RD (~ $3,065,000USD), was a part of a larger public works project that totaled $5,750,000,000RD pesos.<ref name="El Nuevo Diarrio"/>

