{{Infobox stadium | name = Gorodeya Stadium | nickname = | image = ФК Городея.jpg | image_size = 280px | fullname = | location = [[Gorodeya]], [[Minsk Oblast]], [[Belarus]] | coordinates = {{Coord|53|18|24|N|26|30|27|E|region:BY_type:landmark|display=it}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2006 | renovated = 2011, 2016 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[FC Gorodeya]] | operator = | surface = Grass | former_names = | tenants = [[FC Gorodeya]] | capacity = 1,625 | dimensions = 105 x 68 meters | scoreboard = }}
'''Gorodeya Stadium''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Gorodeya]], [[Minsk Oblast]], [[Belarus]]. It is currently used for [[association football|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[FC Gorodeya]]. The stadium holds 1,625 spectators.
==History== The stadium was built and opened in 2006 and has been used by local club [[FC Gorodeya]] ever since. Stadium's original capacity was only 300. After renovations in 2011 additional stands were built to increase capacity to 1,050 and new scoreboard was installed. Further renovations were done in 2016, preparing the stadium for [[Belarusian Premier League]], after which the capacity increased to current 1,625.
==External links== * [http://fcgorodeya.by/klub/stadion Stadium profile at FC Gorodeya website] * [http://www.pressball.by/footballstat/stadiums/32/ Stadium profile at pressball.by]
