{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Jonty Jenner | image = | country = Jersey | fullname = Jonty William Jenner | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|12|4|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Jersey]] | heightft = | heightinch = | heightm = | batting = Right-handed | bowling = Right-arm [[off break]] | role = [[Batting (cricket)|Batsman]] | international = true | internationalspan = 2014–present | columns = 2 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|FC]] | matches1 = 1 | runs1 = 68 | bat avg1 = 68.00 | 100s/50s1 = 0/1 | top score1 = 68 | deliveries1 = – | wickets1 = – | bowl avg1 = – | fivefor1 = – | tenfor1 = – | best bowling1 = – | catches/stumpings1 = 0/– | column2 = [[Twenty20|T20]] | matches2 = 6 | runs2 = 210 | bat avg2 = 52.50 | 100s/50s2 = 0/1 | top score2 = 90[[Not out|*]] | deliveries2 = 6 | wickets2 = 0 | bowl avg2 = – | fivefor2 = – | tenfor2 = n/a | best bowling2 = – | catches/stumpings2 = 2/– | date = 16 June | year = 2017 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/526462.html ESPNcricinfo }}
'''Jonty William Jenner''' (born 4 December 1997) is a professional [[cricket]]er who plays for [[Jersey cricket team|Jersey]].<ref name="Bio">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/526462.html |title=Jonty Jenner |accessdate=7 June 2015 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> On 7 July 2017, he was the substitute fielder for [[Stuart Broad]] during the first [[Test cricket|Test]] between [[South African cricket team in England in 2017|England and South Africa]].<ref name="12thman">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/40505999 |title=England v South Africa: Jersey and Sussex's Jonty Jenner named 12th man |accessdate=7 July 2017 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref>
==Career== In 2014 he played in the [[2014 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] tournament.<ref name="DivFour">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/wcldiv4-2014/content/squad/749627.html |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Four: Jersey Squad |accessdate=7 June 2015 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> He was selected in the Jersey squad for the [[2015 ICC World Twenty20 Qualifier]] tournament<ref name="T20Qual">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/cricket/33022087 |title=Minnows Jersey set for Twenty20 qualifying challenge |accessdate=7 June 2015 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> and the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] matches held in Los Angeles.
He made his [[first-class cricket|first-class]] debut for [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]] against [[South Africa A cricket team|South Africa A]] on 14 June 2017.<ref name="LA">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1099388.html |title=South Africa A tour of England, Tour match: Sussex v South Africa A at Arundel, Jun 14-17, 2017 |accessdate=14 June 2017 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>
In April 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] tournament in Malaysia.<ref name="WCL-Div4">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/cricketinjersey/status/981515595777757184 |title=The 14 man national squad travelling to Malaysia |date=4 April 2018 |accessdate=4 April 2018 |work=Jersey Cricket Board}}</ref><ref name="JerEP">{{cite web|url=https://jerseyeveningpost.com/sport/2018/04/05/chuggys-men-for-mission-to-malaysia/ |title=Chuggy's men for mission to Malaysia |date=5 April 2018 |accessdate=6 April 2018 |work=Jersey Evening Post}}</ref> In August 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018–19 ICC World Twenty20 Europe Qualifier]] tournament in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/45171461 |title=Jersey name squad for World Twenty20 first-round qualifier |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/808096 |title=Three debutants in Jersey squad for ICC World T20 Europe Qualifier |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref>
