{{Infobox company |name = Lucky Strike Lanes |image = File:Lucky Strike Lanes logo.gif |type = [[Privately held company]] |foundation = {{Start date and age|2003}} |location_city = [[Sherman Oaks]], [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] |location_country = U.S. |locations = 18 | industry = Restaurants, Entertainment |area_served = [[North America]] |homepage={{url|http://www.bowlluckystrike.com/}} |}}
'''Lucky Strike''' is a [[bowling alley]] chain operated by '''Lucky Strike Entertainment, LLC''', which owns and operates a chain of facilities that include bowling alleys and billiard parlors, bars, lounges, restaurants and venues for art and music. Founded in 2003, the company is based in [[Sherman Oaks]], [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].<ref>http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=25870783 Bloomberg Businessweek: Company Overview of Lucky Strike Entertainment, LLC</ref>
== History == In 2010 the company and CEO Steven Foster were subjects for an episode of CBS's ''[[Undercover Boss]]''.<ref>http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-505125_162-44740194/undercover-boss-lucky-strike-lanes-steven-foster-rolls-through-the-recession CBS MoneyWatch: "Undercover Boss: Lucky Strike Lanes' Steven Foster Rolls Through the Recession"</ref>
