{{infobox country at games | NPC = MLI | NPCname = National Paralympic Committee of Mali | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Mali|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Mali]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the [[2000 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Sydney]], sending a single representative ([[Facourou Sissoko]]) to compete in powerlifting. In the up to 75kg category, he lifted 130kg - finishing last of the seventeen competitors who successfully lifted a weight. He therefore did not win a medal.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=MLI&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Mali at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
Mali did not compete at the Paralympic Games in 2004. Although he was due to compete in [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008]], as Mali's sole competitor, Sissoko was banned due to testing positive for [[boldenone metabolite]] (a steroid) on the day of the opening ceremony.<ref>[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/paralympics/2008-09/11/content_7020082.htm "Two more Paralympic powerlifters banned for doping"], [[Xinhua]], September 11, 2008</ref>
[[Mahamane Sacko]] represented Mali on the track at the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]], but did not proceed past the heats.
