{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Parc-y-Dwrlyn Ground | nickname = | country = Wales | image = | location = [[Pentyrch]], [[Glamorgan]] | establishment = 1983 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1993 | club1 = [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]] | date = 11 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/90/685.html Ground profile }}
'''Parc-y-Dwrlyn Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Pentyrch]], [[Glamorgan]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1993, when [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]] played [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] in a [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match in the 1993 [[AXA Equity and Law League]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/90/685_a.html List-A Matches played on Parc-y-Dwrlyn Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of [[Pentyrch Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://www.pentyrchcricket.co.uk/ Pentyrch Centurions Cricket Club]</ref> who play in the [[South Wales Cricket League]].
