{{Infobox sports league | title = Tunisian Women's Division I Basketball League | current_season = | logo = | pixels = | caption = | sport = Basketball | founded = 1956 | fame = | motto = | teams = 8 | country = {{flagicon|Tunisia}} [[Tunisia]] | continent = [[FIBA Africa]] ([[Africa]]) | champion = [[Étoile Sportive du Sahel Women's Basketball|Étoile du Sahel]] 1st title (2018) | most_champs = [[CS Sfaxien Women's Basketball|CS Sfaxien]] 18 titles | qualification = | folded = | website = http://ftbb.org.tn/ | singles = | ceo = | TV = }}
The '''Tunisian Women's Division I Basketball League''' is the highest women's professional club basketball competition in [[Tunisia]]. The competition was created in [[1956 in sports|1956]] Just after the Independence of Tunisia Ruled and managed by the [[Tunisian Basketball Federation]], and since it was held every single year until Nowadays, Except only in 1958 season that was cancelled, however the dominant Club is [[CS Sfaxien Women's Basketball|CS Sfaxien]] from [[Sfax]] with a total of 18 titles as a record followed by [[Zitouna Sports (basketball)|Zitouna Sports]] From [[Tunis]] with 8 titles, and third rank we find [[Stade Tunisien (basketball)|Stade Tunisien]] also from [[Tunis]] with 7 Titles<ref>[http://ftbb.org.tn/la-competition/championnat-national-filles/ Championship INFO]</ref>.
